## Lesson 44-3: Question 15 (EXCEPT)

### Before "This is an 'EXCEPT' question":
{{+**Try this:** Attempt the question before reading the analysis below.+}}

### Before the h3 heading:
{{+**Question Type:** EXCEPT -- This question type requires the opposite of the normal approach. Instead of finding one correct answer, confirm that four answers ARE supported by the passage and eliminate the one that is NOT. Work through each choice systematically.+}}

{ "type": "diff-note", "text": "EXCEPT questions require a fundamentally different mental approach. Consider adding a strategy callout explaining: (1) treat each choice as a yes/no question, (2) four will be yes, (3) the one 'no' is the answer. Students frequently rush EXCEPT questions and make careless errors.", "variant": "comment" }

### After the breakdown table:
{{+**EXCEPT Question Strategy:** For every EXCEPT question, mentally rephrase each choice as "Does the passage answer this?" Four will be "yes" -- the one "no" is correct. This systematic approach prevents the common error of selecting the first choice that seems interesting rather than the one truly unsupported.+}}

